[~jgallucci32], the logging:

{code}
2017-10-08 14:31:52  INFO | Activity task for domain LoadbalancingDomain, list LoadBalancerTasks not found
{code}

should really be DEBUG rather than INFO level. Are you seeing any issues on the UFS hosts besides that log message?

To register a simple workflow service instance you would use something like:

{code}
# euserv-register-service -t simpleworkflow -h 10.111.5.61 -z API_10.111.5.61 API_10.111.5.61.simpleworkflow
{code}

where 10.111.5.61 is replaced with the desired IP (i.e. the cloud controller). You can name the "zone" and service as desired, the example above uses the ufs/api convention for service naming.

You would also want to stop (and ultimately deregister) the simple workflow service on the ufs host(s).
